I am trying to create a async function in Blazor WebAssembly project, in preview 8, this worked:

```
  <th @onclick="@(async ()=> await Sort(column.Name))">@column.Name</th>

@code {
    async Task Sort(string column)
    {
        await Http.PostJsonAsync<SelectResult>("Data/Get");
        this.StateHasChanged();
    }
}
```
With 3.0 final release, it does not work anymore. Compiler complains:
Cannot convert lambda expression to type 'object' because it is not a delegate type	AppMaker.Client	...\Pages\Table.razor

Can you please suggest how to do async event with parameters? Thanks very much.

_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/583409/nullable-with-razor-and-cs8632.html)._

